com.csvanefalk.keytestgen.core.oracle
Enum OracleGenerator

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<OracleGenerator>
      com.csvanefalk.keytestgen.core.oracle.OracleGenerator
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<OracleGenerator>
public enum OracleGenerator
extends java.lang.Enum<OracleGenerator>

This singleton provides an API for turning the postconditions of Java methods, represented by KeY Term instances, into test oracles represented by Oracle instances.

Author:
christopher

Constructs an OracleExpression from a Term representing a quantifier, i.e. either FOR-ALL or EXISTS. The bound formula of this quantifier will be simplified to an additional constraint, which makes things more convenient and does not change the semantics of the formula itself.

generateOracle

public Oracle generateOracle(KeYJavaMethod method)
                      throws OracleGeneratorException
Creates a Test Oracle for the provided method. The Oracle will be generated based on the FunctionalOperationContract present for the method, if any. If no such contract exists, a trivial OracleConstraint is generated with no inherent semantic value.

Parameters:
method - the method
Returns:
an OracleConstraint for the method
Throws:
OracleGeneratorException

resolveNumbers

private java.lang.String resolveNumbers(de.uka.ilkd.key.logic.Term term)
Resolves a Term representing a numeric constant function into a corresponding String numeral. For example, Z(0(1(#))) becomes -10.

Parameters:
term - the term
Returns:
the string numeral
